**Affected version**: `7.4` -

`_transform/{id}/_stats` can return a wrong count after a rolling upgrade. This happens only if > 1 config documents exist, which can only happen if the transform got updated with `_transform/{id}/_update`

The issue has been found in upgrade tests, see below.

Root cause: When expanding the id's the hit count is returned for `count` which contains duplicates when config documents for the same transform exist in more than 1 index.

The race only exists for roughly `1s` as old configs get deleted during `_transform/{id}/_update`, the delete call is not waiting for a flush.

